<h3><a name="current"><b>Current Opportunities</b></a></h3>

<p>United HealthCare is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action
Employer. If you are selected as a member of the United
HealthCare team, you will be offered a comprehensive package of
benefits in addition to a competitive salary. </p>

<p>If you are interested in becoming part of one of the nation's
largest health care management services organizations, please
review the following positions and contact us as indicated for
consideration. </p>

<ul>
    <li><a href="#cleric">Clerical</a></li>
</ul>

<ul>
    <li><a href="#clinic">Clinical</a></li>
</ul>

<ul>
    <li><a href="#info">Information Services</a></li>
</ul>

<ul>
    <li>Managerial</li>
</ul>

<ul>
    <li>Sales</li>
</ul>

<ul>
    <li><a href="#prof">Professional</a></li>
</ul>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<hr>

<h3><a name="cleric"><b>Clerical</b></a></h3>

<p><b>Member Services Representative</b> </p>

<ul>
    <li>The member services representative is responsible for
        answering incoming calls from members and providers
        regarding benefits, eligibility and assisting members in
        using the plan correctly. This representative will
        resolve issues such as claim errors, balance billing, and
        member complaints. Qualified candidates will possess
        storing customer service skills, the ability to handle
        multiple priorities, and previous experience in health
        care.</li>
</ul>

<ul>
    <li>Positions available in CA</li>
</ul>

<p align="center"><br>
</p>

<hr>

<h3><a name="clinic"><b>Clinical</b></a></h3>

<p><b>NurseLine Staff Nurse</b> </p>

<ul>
    <li>NurseLine Staff Nurses provide telephonic clinical
        assessment, health education and utilization management
        services to national clients. This service is available
        24 hours a day, seven days a week, including holidays.
        Qualified candidates will have a minimum of three to five
        years of clinical nursing experience in the following
        areas: emergency room, urgent care, pediatric/OB,
        medical/surgical. RN licensure is required.</li>
</ul>

<ul>
    <li>Positions available in MD, MN, TX, VA and WV.</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Utilization Review and Case Management</b> </p>

<ul>
    <li>Our UR and Case Management nurses are primarily
        responsible for inpatient utilization management and
        outpatient case management. This includes a thorough
        assessment and follow through of episodes of care with
        transitions to alternative care levels for assigned
        clients. Qualified candidates will have a minimum of
        three to five years clinical experience. Home health
        experience preferred.</li>
</ul>

<ul>
    <li>Positions available primarily in MN and CA</li>
</ul>

<p align="center"><br>
</p>

<hr>

<h3><a name="info"><b>Information Services</b></a></h3>

<p>With aggressive investment in open systems technology, our
state-of-the-art systems provide the infrastructure that supports
industry-leading health care management products and services for
40 million members. Our core technologies include: </p>

<ul>
    <li>Client/Server: <br>
        Windows, PowerBuilder, C/C++, Sybase, DB2/AIX, IBM
        RS/6000, DCE/Open Systems, TCP/IP, Lotus Suite, Lotus
        Notes, cc:Mail</li>
</ul>

<ul>
    <li>Networks: <br>
        Integrated, LAN/WAN, Window NT, Novell, Unix, IBM,
        Unisys, DCE, HP</li>
</ul>

<ul>
    <li>Mainframe: <br>
        Unisys A Series: COBOL, XGEN, DMS-II. IBM MVS: COBOL,
        DB2, SAS</li>
</ul>

<p>Information Services positions are available in Minneapolis
MN, Hartford CT, Somerset NJ, Greenville SC, St Louis MO, and
Ireland as well as other locations. </p>

<h3><b>Current Positions Include</b></h3>

<P><B>Account Manager</B></P>

<UL>
   <LI><B>Purpose:</B> Manage customer operational functions and
       project queues.<BR>
       <B>Skills:</B> Strong PC, excellent communication (written
       and verbal), client-server design experience.<BR>
       <B>Qualifications:</B> BA, 3 yrs. EDI/EC experience, 3 yrs
       health care experience.
       <P>
       Resume may be sent via the Internet (see below) or to:<BR>
       <BLOCKQUOTE>
       Human Resources<BR>
       United HealthCare Corporation<BR>
       ATTN: VW/Account Manager<BR>
       MN010-W132<BR>
       P.O. Box 1459<BR>
       Minneapolis, MN 55440-1459<BR>
       </BLOCKQUOTE>
</UL>

<p><b>Business Analysts</b> </p>

<ul>
    <li>Progressive positions are available in medical management
        business analysis. This includes translating business
        needs into high level specifications for use in software
        development. Project management and interaction with
        system developers.</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Data Security</b> </p>

<ul>
    <li>System security for three-tier client server technology.
        UNIX, IBM, Unisys.</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Database Management</b> </p>

<ul>
    <li>Progressive roles are available in database management
        include: maintenance of databases on mainframe and micro
        platforms, physical database design and support, data
        modeling, use of systems tools and prototyping.</li>
</ul>

<p><b>PC/LAN Administration</b> </p>

<ul>
    <li>Progressive roles are available in the areas of LAN/WAN
        administration and analysis. These positions grow from
        basic administration and troubleshooting, to B
        microsystems hardware and software operations and design
        to integration of LAN/WAN operations systems.</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Software Engineers</b> </p>

<ul>
    <li>Progressive positions are available in the areas of
        application development. This includes coding, testing,
        debugging, use of software development methodologies,
        establishing of protocols. Often user interaction. Team
        and project oriented roles.</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Technical Communications</b> </p>

<ul>
    <li>Editing responsibilities include creating and maintaining
        technical communications, including all proprietary
        software manuals and training documentation.</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Technical Specialist</b> </p>

<ul>
    <li>Progressive roles in office information systems. These
        include LAN administration and server maintenance, as
        well as LOTUS Notes development.</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Unix System Administration</b> </p>

<ul>
    <li>These positions support United's three-tier client server
        applications. System administrators will typically
        specialize in one or more of the following areas: Unix
        system administration, database administration (Sybase,
        Oracle, DB2/AIX), shell scripting, disaster recovery,
        capacity planning, and more. Knowledge of IBM RS/6000 AIX
        preferred.</li>
</ul>

<p align="center"><br>
</p>

<hr>

<h3><a name="prof"><b>Professional</b></a></h3>

<p><b>Corporate Auditors</b> </p>

<ul>
    <li>As a member of United HealthCare's Corporate Audit staff,
        you are key to our success. You add value by focusing on
        high risk - high return business issues. You work
        collaboratively with management to evaluate business
        controls, drive strategic initiatives, streamline
        business processes and improve compliance programs. <p>You
        are a true professional with a business/accounting
        related college degree and 0-6 years experience in
        corporate or public accounting, audit or operations. Your
        understanding of business processes and controls are
        essential to our success. Your professional credentials
        (MBA, CPA, CISA or CIA), whether current or in process,
        open doors wherever you go. You're a jet-setter who goes
        where the job takes you. And your interest in, or
        knowledge of the managed care, provider or indemnity
        industry makes you a natural candidate for our team!.</p>
    </li>
</ul>

<ul>
    <li>Positions available in Minneapolis, MN.</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h3><a name="employ">Employee Benefits</a></h3>

<p><a>Each and every one of our employees is a key contributor to
the growth and success of United HealthCare. We feel it is
extremely important that you are well compensated for your
efforts, contributions and achievements. In addition to a
competitive salary, you can look forward to one of the most
comprehensive benefit programs in the industry, including: </a></p>

<h4><a name="flexben">Flexible Benefits</a></h4>

<p>These benefits are provided to meet your immediate needs, with
most on a pre-tax basis, including medical, dental, life,
accidental death and dismemberment, dependent life, long term
disability, and health care and dependent care flexible spending
accounts. </p>

<h4><a name="savings">Savings &amp; Retirement Benefits</a></h4>

<p>These benefits are provided to enable you to save and invest
for the future, including the United HealthCare 401(k) Savings
Plan, Employee Stock Ownership Plan and Employee Stock Purchase
Plan. </p>

<h4><a name="life">Life Resource Benefits</a></h4>

<p>These benefits are provided to meet your needs in managing all
aspects of your life, both personal and work. These benefits
include vacation, holidays, sick leave, short term disability
salary continuation, education reimbursement, business travel
accident insurance and an employee assistance program. </p>

<p>But the biggest benefit our program offers is choice. It has
been designed to be flexible, competitive and responsive to life
changes...allowing you to build the coverage that is best for you
and your family...making your life easier and financially more
secure. </p>

<hr>

<h3><a name="submit"><b>Submitting Your Resume</b></a></h3>

<p>We offer two methods for submitting your resume: </p>

<ul>
    <li><b>E-mail:</b> Your E-mail resume should be sent to <a
        href="mailto:resume@uhc.com">resume@uhc.com</a> and be in
        plain ASCII text with a maximum line width of 76
        characters.</li>
</ul>

<ul>
    <li><b>U.S. Mail:</b></li>
</ul>

<p>For Information Services positions please submit resume to: </p>

<ul>
    <li>United HealthCare Corporation <br>
        Human Resources - Information Services/INT<br>
        MN012-S286<br>
        P.O. Box 1459<br>
        Minneapolis, MN 55440-1459</li>
</ul>

<p>For Clinical positions please submit resume to: </p>

<ul>
    <li>United HealthCare Corporation<br>
        Human Resources - Clinical/INT<br>
        MN010-S168<br>
        P.O. Box 1459<br>
        Minneapolis, MN 55440-1459</li>
</ul>

<p>For all other positions please submit resume to:</p>

<ul>
    <li>United HealthCare Corporation<br>
        Staffing Center - INT<br>
        MN012-S286<br>
        P.O. Box 1459<br>
        Minneapolis, MN 55440-1459</li>
</ul>

